    "en": {
      "title": "Exam schedule to be announced in the meeting",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Education Susil Premajayantha announced the dates of Aposa Advanced Level, Aposa Ordinary Level and Grade 5 Scholarship Examination in Parliament today (5).",
        "He announced the dates in response to a question raised by Kegalu District Councilor Mr. Udayakantha Gunathilaka during the adjournment of the House.",
        "\"The results of the last A-level examination will be released in August. The next A-level examination is expected to be held at least three months after the release of the results, probably in November-December. Also, the grade 5 scholarship exam to be held this year is expected to be held on a day before the start of A-level. It is planned to hold the Aposa General Examination at the end of this year in February March next year.",
        "It is necessary to give some period between two main examinations to the examination department to plan the necessary activities. Aposa High Level Examination was held last time. The examination results are in the final stage.",
        "In 2020-21 due to the Covid situation, the school period in the Western Province was lost by about 50 percent. Forty percent of school time was lost in the outer provinces during that time."
      ],
